ring Division.\n\n\nThe incumbent will plan, implement, and oversee the Department’s Capital Improvement Program, including planning, design and construction, reports to the Director, and will assist the Director in the overall administration and management of the Utilities Engineering Division. In addition to managing the Utilities Engineering staff, this position offers an opportunity for hands-on engineering, with responsibility for the design and implementation of more complex projects. Qualified engineers with private sector experience are highly encouraged to apply.\n\n\nDuties may include, but are not limited to, the following:\n\nManages the Utilities Engineering Division, including planning and implementation of Division goals and objectives; selection, training and supervision of personnel; and preparation of multi-year capital improvement program.\nPerforms complex professional engineering and design activities including development and review of detailed facilities design, plans, specifications, contract documents, and cost estimates.\nProvides engineering services during construction.\nOversees selection of and negotiations with engineering consultants and coordinates consultant activities.\nEvaluates and assesses the impacts of proposed development on City water and sewer systems, and develops mitigation measures and conditions of approval.\nRepresents the City in meetings with public officials, the business community and the public, and makes presentations to various groups.\nA complete job description and list of duties can be found at www.hayward-ca.gov\n\n\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\n\n\nAny combination of equivalent experience and education that could likely provide the required knowledge and abilities would qualify. A typical way to obtain the knowledge and abilities are:\n\n\nEXPERIENCE:\n\n\nFive (5) years of increasingly responsible experience in professional engineering work related to the design and construction of water and wastewater projects, including two (2) years of recent supervisory or management experience.\n\n\nEDUCATION:\n\n\nEquivalent to a Bachelor’s degree from an accredited college or university with a major in civil engineering, or closely related engineering field. A Master’s degree in Engineering is desirable.\n\n\nLICENSES AND CERTIFICATES:\n\n\nRegistration as a Professional Engineer (PE) issued by the California State Board of Registration for Professional Engineers. Registration is required upon hire and must be maintained for duration of appointment.\n\n\nPossession and maintenance of a valid California Class C Driver’s License.\n\n\nTHE SELECTION PROCESS\n\n\nCandidates must submit a completed job application and a response to the Supplemental Questions. Application packets will be screened and candidates considered best qualified will move forward to a competitive examination process, which may include a writing exercise and/or an oral interview.\n\n\nThe examination process will result in a ranked eligible register of candidates for hiring consideration by the department. The actual job offer will depend on the candidate’s success in the departmental selection process.","jtr_source":"indeed"}